Introduction

Na Ha-Eun is a South Korean singer and dancer under High Up Entertainment. She made her official debut on January 26th, 2018 with the single "So Special" featuring Microdot.

Na Haeun has done female and male dance covers at the 2017, 2018, and 2019 Melon Music Awards (MMA). During the 2017 Melon Music Awards, she gained popularity for performing a dance cover, 'Peek-A-Boo' by the K-pop girl group, Red Velvet.

Na Haeun has a YouTube channel where she posts covers of female and male dance. She has collaborated with numerous K-pop groups on her channel such as MOMOLAND, GFRIEND, Cherry Bullet, Weeekly, and more.
